def is_bacon_crispy(bacon:item):
    # Function to check if the bacon is crispy
    symbol crispy=exists f: item : is_food(f) and on(f, bacon)
    return crispy

behavior achieve_crispy_bacon(bacon:item, fryingpan:item, stove:item):
    body:
        achieve on(bacon, fryingpan)
        # Ensure bacon is placed on the frying pan
        
        achieve close_char(char, stove)
        # Ensure the stove is in close proximity
        
        if not is_bacon_crispy(bacon):
            # If the bacon is not yet crispy, inspect its state
            observe(fryingpan, "Check if the bacon is crispy")

def is_bacon_crispy(fryingpan:item):
    # Check if the bacon on the frying pan is crispy
    symbol crispy=exists bacon: item : is_fryingpan(fryingpan) and is_food_bacon(bacon) and on(bacon
, fryingpan) and not dirty(bacon)
    return crispy

behavior cook_bacon(fryingpan:item, stove:item):
    body:
        achieve is_on(stove)
        # Ensure stove is on for cooking bacon
        achieve close_char(char, fryingpan)
        # Stay close to the frying pan while cooking

behavior __goal__():
